Very good question! You may transport your musical instrument on any of our flights, provided it is in a secure hard case. Instruments may be transported either as checked baggage or carried with you in the cabin.
If you wish to take the instrument with you on board the plane, it will be counted as hand baggage. Its dimensions must not exceed 55 cm in length x 40 cm in height x 23 cm in width, and it must not weigh more than 8 kg.
If the instrument exceeds these limits, you must contact the Reservations Department to reserve an extra seat, which will be charged at the same fare as your ticket. The applicable charge can be paid at the airport on departure or via the Reservations Department.

For more information, please contact our Call Center (T: 801 11 20000 & +30 210 6261000, available 24/7) and one of my Colleagues will be more than happy to assist you.
In addition, you will be asked to sign a Limited Release Form when you check in the instrument agreeing that the musical instrument is being carried entirely at your own risk.

We do not transfer honey on board, so it must be well packed in tough package, if you want to transfer it in your checked baggage. Otherwise, as a separate bag, in wooden box with absorbent material to prevent leaks which may cause damage to the property of others.
Requesting transportation as a separate bag is mandatory.
Therefore please contact our Call Center (T: 801 11 20000 & +30 210 6261000, available 24/7) and one of my Colleagues will be more than happy to assist you!

We do not transfer @objects as a checked-in baggage.
You can carry your @objects at no charge as a carry-on baggage.
If it exceeds the baggage allowance limits, you need to contact the Reservations Department to reserve an extra seat, which will be charged according to our extra seat pricing policy. The applicable charge can be paid via the Reservations Department.

For more information, please contact our Call Center (T: 801 11 20000 & +30 210 6261000, available 24/7) and one of my Colleagues will be more than happy to assist you!

We provide all the necessary services to ensure that passengers with special needs enjoy a comfortable flight. Wheelchairs are carried free of charge and are not counted as part of the standard baggage allowance.
You can request a wheelchair when you book your ticket or else from 'My Booking' , there is the option to add the special request afterwards.

For any further clarification, please contact our Call Center (T: 801 11 20000 & +30 210 6261000, available 24/7) and one of my Colleagues will be more than happy to assist you!

You can carry electronic cigarettes including e-cigars and other personal vaporizers containing batteries, for personal use, in your carry-on baggage only.
It is prohibited to include electronic cigarettes in checked baggage.

Recharging of these devices and/or batteries on board the aircraft is not permitted and you need to take measures to prevent accidental activation. Spare batteries must be individually protected to prevent short circuits by placing them in the original retail packaging or by otherwise insulating terminals eg by taping over exposed terminals or placing each battery in a separate plastic bag or protective pouch and carried in carry-on baggage only.
You can carry your important papers within the cabin baggage, at no charge.
You can have your laptop and/or your purse under the seat in front of you. There is no charge and there are no specific dimensions. Your purse or backpack shall contain only your personal items.

You can take a carpet as a special baggage on hold. You have to make a request through our Reservations Department (T: 801 11 20000 & +30 210 6261000, available 24/7) to inform you about the cost and the procedure.
